00:05:01.440 --> 00:05:02.650
coming back with
the first thing

00:05:02.650 --> 00:05:03.980
that is the most relevant.

00:05:03.980 --> 00:05:06.210
And obviously, it's just
amazing to think

00:05:06.210 --> 00:05:07.050
where that could go.

00:05:07.050 --> 00:05:08.260
Like, that's one example.

00:05:08.260 --> 00:05:11.190
But you start going deeper and
deeper in and how you can

00:05:11.190 --> 00:05:12.620
start responding to
these queries.

00:05:12.620 --> 00:05:15.050
KRISPY UCCELLO: So developers
often ask, how can I

00:05:15.050 --> 00:05:17.600
participate in the voice
search part of this.

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:19.790
So do you want to talk a
little bit about that?

00:05:19.790 --> 00:05:21.640
MATT GAUNT: At the moment, the
