00:05:35.190 --> 00:05:37.000
automatically like we
do with YouTube.

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:39.080
But at the moment, the Quick
Search Box, you say a voice

00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:41.520
search, it'll come up, it gives
you a list of options.

00:05:41.520 --> 00:05:43.010
And then you can start
having your app

00:05:43.010 --> 00:05:44.300
service at that point.

00:05:44.300 --> 00:05:46.970
So it's still really nice entry
point for a user to kind

00:05:46.970 --> 00:05:48.240
of find your content.

00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:49.950
KRISPY UCCELLO: And what's a
good place for someone who's

00:05:49.950 --> 00:05:51.940
maybe not familiar with
this technology?

00:05:51.940 --> 00:05:53.470
Where should they start
digging in?

00:05:53.470 --> 00:05:56.460
MATT GAUNT: So for me, I think
the best place is to kind of

00:05:56.460 --> 00:05:59.540
start with a really core idea,
a core concept you think

00:05:59.540 --> 00:06:02.320
people will really benefit
from and love.

00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:04.170
And then start developing
an Android app.

00:06:04.170 --> 00:06:07.090
And if you start getting to
that point where you can

00:06:07.090 --> 00:06:10.660
release something and publish
it, do it as soon as possible

00:06:10.660 --> 00:06:12.400
when you're comfortable with
it, like you think it's

00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:13.480
actually good enough.

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:15.310
Because what you start learning
is people will start

00:06:15.310 --> 00:06:17.650
responding with feature requests
or they'll start

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:19.970
finding out bugs that you
haven't found yourself.

00:06:19.970 --> 00:06:21.940
And then you quickly start
learning about the platform,

00:06:21.940 --> 00:06:26.670
you start learning the nuances
of the APIs, et cetera.

00:06:26.670 --> 00:06:28.860
And for me, that's the easiest
way of doing it, is if you

00:06:28.860 --> 00:06:31.200
start learning on the job, you
start getting people feeding

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:33.556
back to everything that
you're doing.

00:06:33.556 --> 00:06:34.170
It's much more organic.

00:06:34.170 --> 00:06:35.010
KRISPY UCCELLO: So measurement
is obviously

00:06:35.010 --> 00:06:36.210
a big part of this.

00:06:36.210 --> 00:06:38.890
So analytics, mobile
analytics, APIs

00:06:38.890 --> 00:06:40.290
would play a big role.

00:06:40.290 --> 00:06:42.850
But just back to the search
box for a moment.

00:06:42.850 --> 00:06:45.970
There's a section in Android
documentation about this?

00:06:45.970 --> 00:06:48.810
MATT GAUNT: Yep, so I think
literally if you go to

00:06:48.810 --> 00:06:52.700
developers.android.com, there's
a massive search box

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:53.230
right there.

00:06:53.230 --> 00:06:54.660
Search Quick Search Box.

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:57.100
Generally, the documentation on
the Android site is great

00:06:57.100 --> 00:06:59.480
because you don't just get
an API doc generally.

00:06:59.480 --> 00:07:02.160
