KRISPY UCCELLO: So one
last thing that

00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:24.700
we should talk about.

00:09:24.700 --> 00:09:27.000
What do you think developers
of TV apps should pay

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:29.065
attention to out of
CES this year?

00:09:29.065 --> 00:09:31.320
MATT GAUNT: I think the biggest
kind of thing that

00:09:31.320 --> 00:09:34.360
you'll notice when you start
looking at any kind of TV

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:37.460
platform is generally, they try
and make things as simple

00:09:37.460 --> 00:09:39.480
and kind of relaxing
as possible.

00:09:39.480 --> 00:09:42.620
Like people who are in the
living room interacting with

00:09:42.620 --> 00:09:45.990
their TVs, they're trying
to get to some form of

00:09:45.990 --> 00:09:46.900
entertainment, generally.

00:09:46.900 --> 00:09:48.970
They're in that kind of mode
where they just want to relax

00:09:48.970 --> 00:09:51.300
and just be entertained.

00:09:51.300 --> 00:09:54.330
And I think the biggest that
developers need to take away

00:09:54.330 --> 00:09:58.720
from that is, whatever you do
with your UI, try and keep it

00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:01.920
simplistic, try and focus more
on your core functionality and

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:04.710
make it as seamless as possible
to get the user from

00:10:04.710 --> 00:10:07.310
entry to where they want
to go in your app.

00:10:07.310 --> 00:10:10.100
So for me, it's all about
focusing on the experience and

00:10:10.100 --> 00:10:13.430
making sure what they're doing,
they're enjoying, and

00:10:13.430 --> 00:10:15.740
just trying to create some
sort of environment and

00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:17.240
experience where they're
really enjoying it.

00:10:17.240 --> 00:10:18.550
KRISPY UCCELLO: And that's
really what it comes down to--

00:10:18.550 --> 00:10:19.920
create an experience.

